He pointed out that Quebec’s development was largely determined by the relationship with the North: the gold rush in Abitibi, the design work in Quebec, the James Bay...
"This is ours, our future!" he added, after taking a theatrical break and looking at the huge map behind his back.
The North, which covers 70% of Quebec’s territory, also includes part of Labrador, which Quebec has always demanded for itself, the Prime Minister said at the press conference.
