Close ties between politics and 'ndrangheta, the mayor of Gioia Tauro arrested
"The mayor of Gioia Tauro supported the interests of the Piromalli clan in municipal decisions."
Serious charges were made by the judges of the Anti-Mafia Directorate in Calabria against the mayor and deputy mayor of Gioia Tauro, Giorgio Dal Torrione and Rosario Schiavone, and the mayor of Rosarno Carlo Martelli, who were arrested this morning on charges of external involvement in a criminal network.
Cuffs were placed in the hands of Gioacchino Piromalli, a senior mediator between the clan and the administration, as well as a lawyer nephew with the same name as the boss, who had previously been convicted of participating in a mafia-like criminal network and was compensated for EUR 10 million.
"The disregard for all legal and moral rules, even good taste," the state's attorneys wrote. The two local governments declared their intention to pay an advisory fee to Piromalli's lawyer.
"Thus, the clan would have had official access to the city hall, which would have given us an additional opportunity to control and control the administration, which is already significant.
